SIMPLE: shifting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shifting
<hw>Shift"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Changing in place,
position, or direction; varying; variable; fickle; <as>as,
<ex>shifting</ex> winds; <ex>shifting</ex> opinions or
principles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Adapted or used for shifting anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shifting backstays</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>,
<cd>temporary stays that have to be let go whenever the vessel tacks or
jibes.</cd> -- <col><b>Shifting ballast</b></col>, <cd>ballast which may
be moved from one side of a vessel to another as safety requires.</cd>
-- <col><b>Shifting center</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Metacenter</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Shifting locomotive</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Switching
engine</cref>, under <er>Switch</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shiftingly</ent>⟦br⟧
